ScheduleItem.Synopsis: Sixteen strangers head back to summer camp to relive the most magical time of their lives. From the ugly duckling turned fashion model, to the nerdy Eagle Scout looking to show the world what geeks can do, to the Miami firefighter who grew up pranking girls, all of these campers came to play. And this time around they’ll be competing against each other in a summer-long “Battle of the Sexes” for a $250,000 prize.

After first round elimination votes are announced, the men believe there is a rat among them! With one rogue vote, suspicions grow about who went behind the group’s back. Summer romance ignites between campers at the poolside weekly camp social. Camp counselor elections get heated when there’s a tie and one camper betrays the other to win the title. This week’s color war is s’more inspired. In the end, another camper is sent packing.
An unwelcome surprise has Connor hunting a mole at V3. Dani counsels an accountant with a big secret. Paloma wants to get on the fast track. TK's new relationship with Sheera heats up.

Annie must determine how to balance two new relationships in her life – a burgeoning romance with Auggie and a professional partnership with Henry Wilcox – while also searching within Colombia for a new person of interest: the Puma.
While the NCIS team deals with Kate's death, Gibbs' determination to finally put an end to Ari's (guest star Rudolf Martin) reign of terror mounts, on the third season premiere of NCIS.
Ari (guest start Rudolf Martin) continues to wreak havoc on the NCIS team, as he uses its members as pawns in the game he's playing with Gibbs.
A search for the killer of one of their own puts all the agents at risk.
The team continues to race against the clock as they hunt for the killer who took the life of one of their own.
A shocking revelation comes to light after the team is forced into playing a dangerous war game.
The team must rely on information from some questionable individuals to stop a criminal bent on stealing government secrets.

A Marine Colonel is killed on a military golf course, leading the NCIS team to pair up with the Army Criminal Investigative Unit in order to find the killer. After the CIA receives a tip about an abandoned warehouse rigged to explode, McGee uses his computer knowledge to get into the CIA informant database to uncover the terrorist cell.

After 10 kilograms of toxic chemicals go missing, Gibbs and the team must race against the clock to find it before it's too late. The team is shocked when they discover that the weapon is in the possession of Mamoun Sharif, a wanted terrorist.

Michael and Fiona pose as hackers at a malicious programming syndicate in order to steal information for Sonya. But Michael’s life gets complicated when working with Fiona again brings back painful memories. Meanwhile, Sam and Jesse help Barry track down a former girlfriend in exchange for falsified documents.
